<span id="fn_380"></span>[115:381](2010056.htm#fr_380.md) <span
id="iii.vii.xv-p8.1"></span>

<span id="iii.vii.xv-p9"></span> The significance of the word
“immediately” as employed here is somewhat dark. There is no event
described in the preceding context with which it can be connected. I am
tempted to think that Eusebius may have been using at this point some
unknown source and that the word “immediately” refers to an encounter
which Simon had had with Peter (perhaps his Cæsarean discussion,
mentioned in the Clementines), of which an account was given in the
document employed by Eusebius. The figure employed here is most
remarkable.

