<span id="fn_382"></span>[115:383](2010056.htm#fr_382.md) <span
id="iii.vii.xv-p11.1"></span>

<span id="iii.vii.xv-p12"></span> Rome was a great gathering place of
heretics and schismatics. They were all attracted thither by the
opportunities for propagandism which the city afforded, and therefore
Eusebius, with his transcendental conception of heresy, naturally makes
it the especial seat of the devil.

<span id="fn_383"></span>[115:384](2010056.htm#fr_383.md) <span
id="iii.vii.xv-p12.1"></span>

